The paper discusses a technique for identifying and healing data loss problems in Android apps, which involves checking the correct recovery of states at run-time. This topic is related to software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of incorrect implementation of state-saving mechanisms, which can lead to security vulnerabilities (cs.CR) and performance issues (cs.DC).
